tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review: I had had a childhood fear of dentists ever since I was a child and consequently, I had neglected my teeth too.Dr Rane is the first dentist that I have ever been to and the man has not only helped me with the cavities but his friendly demeanour has me finally over my fear of Dentists.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
Dr. Rane is understanding and listens to your problem intently. My first appointment for just a checkup of tooth pain was fruitful as he did the necessary xrays, explained the problem, the remedial procedure required and the costs involved. His inputs helped me take a decision and I booked the appointment with him in the next 5 days for wisdom tooth extraction as well as root canal of the adjoining tooth damaged by the wisdom tooth. I had 3 appointments post that - 

Appointment 1 - 1 hr sitting. Wisdom tooth extraction was tricky but was completed successfully. Required stitches post the operation. The adjoining tooth was then prepared for root-canal by removing the infected tissues and medicine being applied. I followed the instructions of the doctor post the operation regarding food intake and cold compression so faced very little swelling and almost no pain (if you take all the medicines on the time).

Appointment 2 - 45 mins sitting. Stitches were removed. Tooth was checked if the infection had gone completely post which it was shaved and impression was taken for the crown .

Appointment 3 -  15 mins sitting. The new crown was nicely fit in place.

Doctor was supportive through all the sittings and during the procedures.  He will not recommend anything if not necessary. Definitely recommended.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
context: RCT - Root Canal Treatment,Wisdom Tooth Extraction,
review: Dr. Prasad Rane is the best when it comes to dental care. Super hygienic clinic well skill staff and excellent latest equipment's.  I did my treatment for Root canal and Wisdom tooth extraction.  it was painless  procudure and DR. Prasad did it with some magical powers as if nothing had happened. Dr. Prasad Rane is a talented person who knows his patient problem and can identify the cure quickly.  When it comes to dental problem without any second thought go and visit My Smile Dental Clinic. Kudos to Dr, Prasad  Rane and his team . Regards,

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,
review: Dr. Prasad Rane is one dentist who saved my fractured and infected tooth. Every dentist had told me that there is no chance to save it but he tried and successfuly saved my tooth. He did repeat rct and caping after partially extracting the fractured part. I am currently visiting him for my wisdom tooth and adjacent tooth decay problem. In the very first sitting, I feel better, and the acute never ending pain is in control. He is always ready to help and for me, he is the dentist I can trust completely. Thank you doctor.

I had gone to the doctor for my filling which had come out. The doctor told me that the filling was big and would require 2 fillings which I found a little surprising because he ended up doing 1 filling only eventually.

Also, I clearly remember him telling me it is 900 per filling so total Rs 1,800. But when I went to pay the money, he told me its 1,800 per filling so total of Rs 3,600. Even if I give the benefit of doubt of miscommunication, *** *** *** ******* **** * ******** ** ***** *** **** *** charging me for 2 filling when doing only 1 filling ** ***** ** ****** * ***** *** ****** * **** *** * * * ** *******
This was the 2nd time I went to this doctor because I found him friendly and economical in first go. But the 2nd experience has been quite disturbing I would say. Did not appreciate the dishonesty of mentioning 1 amount and charging another in the end. I seriously feel I should have not gone here and will never go again.

If you are planning to visit, will highly recommend to clearly ask the total cost twice before proceeding for any treatment.
reply_text:
Dear Siddharth, 
We are surprised to see this review. We did repeat of the broken fillings done by the previous other dentist before. The fees were clearly  mentioned before starting the procedure ( as a protocol, we mention the fees before doing any treatment for all our patients) After removing the filling, dr realised that adjacent tooth also has developed the cavity and needs attention and dr completed both the fillings only after your consent for the same including fees.
Off course the treatment rendered to you in both appointments were different and so was the fees.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
I was petrified of Dentists throughout my childhood days and that kept me away from  all the dentists , for almost 10 years!! After Much persuasion  by my wife I agreed to visit Dr Prasad Rane as she had already visited him in the past! 
From the time I entered till I left everything was pleasant, Dr Rane's way of listening to you and calming you down about your phobia of dentists to his treatment everything was excellent!
I would highly recommend My Smile Dentist to anyone who's been wanting to go to a Dentist who could comfort you rather than scare you !!

tags: Treatment satisfaction,Explanation of the health issue,
review: I had a single sitting root canal treatment done at Dr Rane's clinic. The process is almost painless, you might have a little pain with the rubber clamp while getting the root canal but that goes away as soon as the clamp is removed. The process took around 80-90 mins to do the full thing which included filling  two of my cavities as well. After getting root canal I had problem because of unevenness in the filling which was placed as a placeholder until the capping was done, it was a minor issue but as I could not visit the doctor I used to have pain while chewing. Dr Rane fixed that issue in less than 30 seconds. The capping process was very fast just 10-15 mins visit was all it took to get it done, although it might take up to 30-40 mins for the pre capping procedure which includes taking the measurement and preparing the space for capping. It has been five days now and it feels as if my tooth was never infected it is as normal as it used to be.

As I had been a little scared after being advised by a couple of dentists to go for the wisdom tooth removal surgery -
the type of dental issue, absolutely all of us fear the most -
One of my colleagues told me to go to Dr. Rane with blind trust.
So, when I visited him, I was pretty impressed and pacified by the amount of time and genuine concern and attention he gives to hear you out, examine and explain the dental issue.
His immensely friendly nature made me confident to go for the surgery without procrastination.
And then in an unbelievable experience, I couldn't even properly notice when the surgery started and ended. It was that painless. And it's been a day after the surgery now, and it still is painless now with the prescribed medication. With quite a lot of comfort now, I think I'm going to get back to office within a day or two.
Highly recommend Dr. Rane.
reply_text: Thanks a lot for your feedback. It means a lot to us.

tags: Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Doctor friendliness,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
It's highly essential to explain concerned problem and best possible solution of that particular problem.

In my case, I was explained my tooth problem in simple layman's language and best possible solution of Dental Implant was suggested by Dr. Prasad Rane.

Also, when I asked about the cist of implant, he explained me that Dental Implant starts from 28,000/- and also explained me that he can let me know about exact cost of Implant only after the tooth scan.

I got satisfaction in the first visit itself and today I have a followup at Doctor's Dental Clinic.

The clinic is 5 minutes from my residence and this is added benefit.

I highly recommend Dr. Prasad Rane. Please visit his Dental Clinic and get best treatment.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review: I have been having a great relation with Dr. Prasad Rane at My Smile Dental clinic for almost 8 years now. I have had my root canal treatments, wisdom tooth extractions, dental fillings and teeth cleaning with polishing done at his clinic. Amazingly, he seems to always have all my necessary dental records - big or small, that he has performed on me since the very beginning. That way he has access to my dental history at his fingertips. He makes me feel relaxed and worry free and all of the above mentioned procedures have been super comfortable and almost pain-free for me. He has been upgrading himself with changing times and has all the advanced tools and machines The clinic is always hygienic following covid protocols with a welcoming and friendly staff.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review: *** ****** **** ** ******** *** **** ******* ** *** ****** It's not just his craft he is fabulous at, it's his charm, his communication, his care and his counsel. From making a patient feel absolutely at ease with an assurance that nothing can be too bad, that everything has a solution to the execution of his schedule, he and his team are incomparable. I have reason to believe he has wizard hands... I got some elaborate work done at his clinic without an iota of pain or discomfort. Instead, he made it feel like home, right down to the music that he plays as he works his magic! His setup is spick and span with all measures and protocol of safety and hygiene in place. His equipment and technology seem to the finest I have known or seen. His team is extremely cooperative and courteous. They will always meet you with a solution and a smile :)

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
Dr. Prasad Rane’s approach is very comforting. His treatment philosophy always is “let’s retain the natural tooth as much as we can”. I went to him for a second opinion for a root canal therapy and after thorough evaluation and weighing all options, based on his suggestion I went for filling as the cavity exposure to root was very minimal. He was honest that “the filling may fail, but it is worth giving a shot as it would help retain the natural tooth”. Went for filling and no problem even after an year. Now Dr. Prasad is favourite dentist of my daughter too. She says “even after growing up, where ever I am, if I have to go to a dentist, I will go to Dr. Prasad only” :)
His clinic is very clean and well equipped and his staff are also very courteous and helpful.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Wait time,
review:
****** ** **** *************, witty, smart and at the same time patient-friendly and down to earth. He clearly assesses the problem statement and then provides the best solution available while giving pros and cons of alternate treatments. This helps the patient to build confidence in the treatment.
Dr is very polite and generous person. He'll take every effort to explain the root cause, treatment and post treatment precaution. He's never in a hurry to rush appointments. 
The clinic is very clean with utmost levels of hygiene maintained. The helping staff is also very courteous, well trained and professional.
I visited for my grandmother's(82yrs) denture. Since the doctor is also a professor he sought the best available option to provide her the best type of fixture. As of a week now after using the new set of dentures, she's very satisfied with the overall procedure.
I'll definitely REFER & RECOMMEND Dr for a 100% satisfactory dental treatment

Will highly recommend him to others out there.

The doctor was very nice, and explained everything in detail before going with the procedure. He also adjusted my treatment in in his schedule so that I can complete the procedure as soon as possible without causing an hindrance to my work schedule.  
The procedure was a little on the costly side, but given the quality of the procedure and the doctor's experience, it was worth its value. Overall a very comfortable experience; the clinic was also very clean and comfortable, making the treatment feel highly qualified.

review: As I am under treatment for cirrhosis of liver, the Doctor has requested to get opinion of treating doctor about administering antibiotic dose.

I have been hesitant to go to dentist after my last implant torture few years ago. Almost after 7 years I found a dentist on web with major reviews and I immediately decided to consult him and that was Dr Prasad Rane. In my first experience I found a dentist who checked each and every tooth which gave me an amazing confidence that he is a professional and not the types who would just check what you show as issue, that proves how professionally concerned he is with your complete oral health. With his expertise I got a very painless root canal done and moreover my pain area that was capping on the implant tooth which was beautifully fixed with no bridging at all (as suggested by earlier 3 dentists that I had consulted) Overall an amazing experience.. Truly worth the visit !!!

context: Teeth Whitening,Porcelain inlays and onlays,Porcelain Veneers,
review:
Dr Rane explained the treatments in question in detail and found him very precise in his work. He was helpful to me, considering things from my point of view. !!

I went to Dr Rane for Porcelain Veneers. However, having checked my teeth condition, he strongly advised be against it. Ended up with doing whitening instead :P. 

I have been to couple of other Dentists who would try to get as much money out as they can by suggesting treatments that I guess were not in my best interest. Certainly not the case with Dr Rane at My Smile Dental Clinic.

I would strongly suggest Dr Rane to others.

I have been visiting Dr. Rane since little over 6 months now and amongts the many dentists I have visited, Dr. Rane has the best hands in the profession! He is hands down one of the best dentist I have visited. Be it any ailment (root canal, implant, cavity filing, alignment and more) Dr. Rane is brilliant in all treatments and well equipped with the latest technology at his clinic. He has a knack to treat his cases with supreme perfection, during my treatment for alignment and cleaning I had the most painless and best experience! I would highly recommend Dr. Rane to everyone as I have had one of the best dental experiences with him.
